                                "stop": 9.474,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 144426,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has an opinion this morning in case 09-6338, Dillon vs. United States."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.474,
                        "stop": 214.1,
                        "byte_start": 144426,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15131,
                            "name": "Sonia Sotomayor",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/sonia_sotomayor",
                            "last_name": "Sotomayor",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2776,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1249707600,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": null,
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2776"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32685,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 50379,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/sonia_sotomayor_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 2293,
                            "identifier": "sonia_sotomayor"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.474,
                                "stop": 20.986,
                                "byte_start": 144426,
                                "byte_stop": 190506,
                                "text": "In 1993, petitioner Percy Dillon was convicted of among other things, crack cocaine offenses and was sentenced to 322 months imprisonment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.986,
                                "stop": 31.221,
                                "byte_start": 190506,
                                "byte_stop": 231466,
                                "text": "Roughly fifteen years later, the sentencing commission amended the Crack Cocaine Guidelines by lowering them and it made the amendments retroactive."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.221,
                                "stop": 39.087,
                                "byte_start": 231466,
                                "byte_stop": 262917,
                                "text": "Dillon then moved for sentence reduction under 18 USC code Section 3582 (C) (2)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.087,
                                "stop": 51.926,
                                "byte_start": 262917,
                                "byte_stop": 314222,
                                "text": "That provision authorizes a District Court to reduce an otherwise final sentence pursuant to a guideline amendment if a reduction is consistent with the commission\u0027s policy statements."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.926,
                                "stop": 71.036,
                                "byte_start": 314222,
                                "byte_stop": 390708,
                                "text": "The relevant policy statement found in section 1B1.10 of the Guidelines Manual precludes a court from reducing a sentence to a term that is less than the minimum of the amended guidelines range except in circumstances not applicable here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.036,
                                "stop": 88.485,
                                "byte_start": 390708,
                                "byte_stop": 460507,
                                "text": "Dillon nevertheless asked the district court to impose a sentence below the amended range, contending that our decision in United States versus Booker which made the guidelines advisory requires court to treat section 1B110 as nonbinding."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.485,
                                "stop": 97.011,
                                "byte_start": 460507,
                                "byte_stop": 494571,
                                "text": "He also asked the court to correct certain alleged errors in his original sentence that are unrelated to the guidelines amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.011,
                                "stop": 105.482,
                                "byte_start": 494571,
                                "byte_stop": 528426,
                                "text": "The District Court imposed a sentence at the bottom of the revised guideline range but declined to grant the further reduction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.482,
                                "stop": 117.849,
                                "byte_start": 528426,
                                "byte_stop": 577954,
                                "text": "Finding Booker inapplicable to section 3582(C)(2), the court concluded that section 1B110 constrained it to impose a sentence within the amended range."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.849,
                                "stop": 120.915,
                                "byte_start": 577954,
                                "byte_stop": 590179,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.915,
                                "stop": 128.295,
                                "byte_start": 590179,
                                "byte_stop": 619750,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to address Bookers\u0027 applicability to section 3582 (C) (2) proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.295,
                                "stop": 139.912,
                                "byte_start": 619750,
                                "byte_stop": 666248,
                                "text": "Dillon contends that proceedings under that section are essentially plenary re-sentencing proceedings and that Booker\u0027s holdings therefore apply."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.912,
                                "stop": 144.125,
                                "byte_start": 666248,
                                "byte_stop": 683071,
                                "text": "The text and purpose of the statute belay that claim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.125,
                                "stop": 154.544,
                                "byte_start": 683071,
                                "byte_stop": 724762,
                                "text": "Section 3582 (C) (2) represents a congressional act of lenity intended to give prisoners the benefit of later enacted guidelines amendments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 154.544,
                                "stop": 167.768,
                                "byte_start": 724762,
                                "byte_stop": 777634,
                                "text": "The authority of the courts acting under section 3582 (C) (2) is substantially constrained by the commission which is charged with determining whether and to what extent the guidelines amendment is retroactive."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.768,
                                "stop": 177.148,
                                "byte_start": 777634,
                                "byte_stop": 815146,
                                "text": "By statute, the court may exercise discretion to reduce a prisoner sentence only to the extent consistent with the commission\u0027s statements."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.148,
                                "stop": 188.05,
                                "byte_start": 815146,
                                "byte_stop": 858718,
                                "text": "In light of these unique constraints, it is clear that proceedings authorized under section 3582 (C) (2) are not re-sentencing proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 188.05,
                                "stop": 203.614,
                                "byte_start": 858718,
                                "byte_stop": 920994,
                                "text": "For the reasons elaborated in our opinion issued today we hold that treating section (1) (B) 110 as binding in these circumstances implicates neither the sixth amendment nor remedial interest that issue in Booker."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 203.614,
                                "stop": 207.548,
                                "byte_start": 920994,
                                "byte_stop": 936772,
                                "text": "Accordingly, the judgment of the Court of Appeals is affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.548,
                                "stop": 214.1,
                                "byte_start": 936772,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed a dissenting opinion, Justice Alito took no part in the decision of the court."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
